            "Madame Gautreau was an American expatriate, born Virginie Amélie Avegno in Louisiana, adding an intriguing layer of cross-cultural identity to her Parisian socialite status.",
            "The painting was not sold until 1916, when Sargent sold it to the Metropolitan Museum of Art, where it has since become one of their most celebrated works.",
