            "Vermeer used expensive pigments for this work, including ultramarine derived from lapis lazuli, a luxury material at the time.",
            "The painting was relatively unknown until the late 19th century when it was rediscovered and exhibited, quickly gaining fame.",
            "Vermeer produced only about 36 known paintings, making each one, including 'Girl with a Pearl Earring,' incredibly precious and rare."
